## 8. Your Privacy Rights

If you are a California resident or a resident of another US state with a comprehensive privacy law, you have the following rights regarding your personal information:

### 8.1 Right to Know

You may request information about:
- Categories of personal information we have collected about you
- Specific pieces of personal information we hold
- Categories of sources
- Business or commercial purposes for collection
- Categories of third parties with whom we share

### 8.2 Right to Delete

You may request deletion of personal information we collected from you, subject to certain exceptions (e.g., legal compliance, fraud prevention).

### 8.3 Right to Correct

You may request correction of inaccurate personal information we maintain about you.

### 8.4 Right to Opt-Out of Sale or Sharing

You may opt out of the sale or sharing of your personal information (see Section 7.2).

{{#if collectsSensitivePI}}
### 8.5 Right to Limit Use of Sensitive Personal Information

You may direct us to use your SPI only for necessary purposes (see Section 4).
{{/if}}

### 8.6 Right to Data Portability

You may request a copy of personal information in a portable, machine-readable format (JSON or CSV).

### 8.7 Right to Non-Discrimination

We will not discriminate against you for exercising any of these rights. We do not deny services, charge different prices, or provide different quality based on privacy rights exercise.

## 9. How to Exercise Your Rights

### 9.1 Submission Methods

- **Online form**: {{rightsRequestUrl}}
{{#if hasTollFree}}
- **Toll-free number**: {{tollFreeNumber}}
{{/if}}
- **Email**: {{contactEmail}}
- **Mail**: {{operatorAddress}}

### 9.2 Verification

We will verify your identity before processing requests. Verification may require matching 2-3 data points we already have (e.g., email, name, recent activity). For "Right to Know" requests for specific pieces of information, additional verification may be required.

### 9.3 Authorized Agent

You may designate an authorized agent to submit requests on your behalf. We require:
- Written permission signed by you
- Agent verification of their identity

### 9.4 Response Time

We will confirm receipt within **10 business days** and respond within **45 calendar days**. Extensions of up to 45 additional days are possible with notice (maximum 90 days total).

